<HEADLINE> LIFFE Trades 20 Million Contracts in September </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 2 (Xinhua) -- The London International
Financial Futures and Options Exchange (LIFFE) traded a record of
20.1 million contracts in September, a rise of 43 percent over the
same 1996 period.
</P>
<P>
This means that the exchange, for the first time, has traded
more contracts than any other exchange in the world, according to
LIFFE officials.
</P>
<P>
Statistics released today show that average daily volume
amounted to 913,872 contracts, representing a daily nominal
turnover of 217.96 billion pounds (350 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Jack Wigglesworth, Chairman of LIFFE, said "It is only by
adapting to change and in meeting market needs that financial
market can be successful. It is LIFFE's ability to provide a
deeply liquid, efficient and safe market in the recent uncertainty
over European interest rates."
</P>
<P>
The achievement also reflected the growing importance of Europe
in international capital markets, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
