<BODY>
<HEADLINE> African Championships Canceled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, October 2 (Xinhua) -- The 1997 African Gymnastic
Championships were called off because no enough countries would
send their athletes to participate scheduled for Algeria next
month, it was said by the head of the sport in South Africa
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Algeria has been plagued with persistent and ongoing
violence. Hugo Olivier, president of the South African Gymnastics
Federation, announced their withdrawal.
</P>
<P>
Last year's championships, scheduled to take place in Egypt,
also were canceled at the last minute.
</P>
<P>
South Africa was the reigning team champions of the
competition, which began in 1990 in Egypt. 
</P>
</TEXT>
