<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe to Keep Training Foreign Military </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, October 2 (Xinhua) -- The Zimbabwe Defense Ministry
will continue to train foreign military officers at its staff
college as this reduces regional tensions and misunderstandings,
Defense Minister Moven Mahachi said today.
</P>
<P>
Mahachi said continued enrollment of students from neighboring
countries had brought innumerable benefits to Zimbabwe and the
sub-region.
</P>
<P>
He was speaking at a joint graduation ceremony of the 31st
junior staff course and second workshop commanders at Zimbabwe
Staff College.
</P>
<P>
''We all recognize that this system enhances peaceful
collaboration, mutual cooperation and understanding which are
essential and categorical prerequisites for peace, tranquillity
and unimpeded development in the entire sub-region,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
Fifty-four students including two officers from Ghana and
Malawi graduated from the junior staff course.
</P>
<P>
Mahachi said later this year students from Rwanda, Seychelles
and Uganda would be part of the enrollment for the next course.
</P>
<P>
The junior staff course started in June this year. The course
syllabus included subjects on peace-keeping, computer training
and management information systems. 
</P>
</TEXT>
