<HEADLINE> WBO Super-Middleweight champion Collins Retires </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 2 (Xinhua) -- Steve Collins of Ireland gave up
defending his WBO super-middleweight title as he announced his
retirement on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The 32-year-old Collins was expected to fight against WBC light
heavyweight champion Roy Jones Jr.. However, he showed no
interestes in defending his title for the eighth time.
</P>
<P>
"I don't have the motivation that I once had," Collins was
quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Collins, who has a match record of 36 wins and three loses, has
pulled out of the bout against Britain's Joe Calzaghe scheduled on
October 11. The vacant title will be decided after contest between
Calzaghe and Eubank of Welsh. 
</P>
</TEXT>
