<HEADLINE> EC Adopts Promotion Programs for Quality Beef </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, October 2 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU)'s
executive arm, the European Commission, has adopted a total of 23
action programs to promote market quality beef, it was learned
here today.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of these promotion measures is estimated at 14.7
million ECUs (some 19 million U.S. dollars), three fifths of which
will be financed by the Commission.
</P>
<P>
The programs were adopted on a proposal from Mr. Franz
Fischler, EU commissioner for agriculture and rural development,
according to a press release issued here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
These programs are added to the other 13 which were adopted in
April 1997 and worth 18.5 million ECUs (about 24 million dollar).
</P>
<P>
The programs, which for the first time ever do not only concern
quality beef but also quality veal, comprise a number of
promotional activities which include publicity measures in radio
and TV, publicity measures in magazines and papers and promotional
activities at the points of sales.
</P>
<P>
The Commission says that the promotional strategy is mainly
aimed to reassure consumers and increase consumer confidence in
the value of quality beef, guarantee the existence of full and
independent control from the producer to the consumer and to
increase the market share of quality beef. 
</P>
</TEXT>
