<HEADLINE> Tanzania Aims at Developing Lake Victoria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, October 2 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania has expressed
stronger wishes to develop infrastructure facilities at the Lake
Victoria, the second largest freshwater lake in the world.
</P>
<P>
The Tanzanian government is working closely with other eastern
African states in this sector, Batholomeo Rufunjo, Marine
Transport Director with the Ministry of Communications and
Transport, said here today.
</P>
<P>
Several investors have required detailed information on market
potentials and technical information such as on navigation charts
and communication systems, the official said.
</P>
