in Pretoria on Monday, Malami restated the commitments of both
countries to provide the framework and enabling environment for
mutual collaboration toward the economic enhancement of the
continent.
</P>
<P>
Efforts were also on to promote the rich cultures of both
countries, the envoy said, adding that Nigeria intended to bring
about an active and sustained exchanges of sporting teams and
cultural troupes between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The relations between the two countries, which came to its
bottom in 1995 when South Africa spearheaded a suspension of
Nigeria's membership in the Commonwealth, has begun to warm up
recently.
</P>
<P>
Nigerian Foreign Minister Tom Ikimi visited Pretoria last
month with a message of Nigerian head of state General Sani
Abacha for President Nelson Mandela.
</P>
<P>
In return, South Africa's Vice-President Thambo Mbeki is
expected to make a trip to Nigeria at an undisclosed date. Mbeki
was originally scheduled to visit Nigeria on September 17-18, but
the timetable was changed for reasons of convenience.  
