</P>
<P>
In Paris, the CAC-40 index shed early gains to end 2.86 points
down at 3,052.07, tracking a softer dollar and an early decline in
the Dow.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that the market was cautious ahead of US September
jobs figures due on Friday and a national jobs conference on
October 10.
</P>
<P>
However, German shares sustained Wednesday's gains and ended
stronger after an early mark-up but off best levels in subdued
trading ahead of a market holiday and US economic data.
</P>
<P>
The DAX-30 index closed at 4,273.71, up 76.73 points. 
