<HEADLINE> French President Calls on Italy to Help Algeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 3 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
today called on Italy to use its influence to help Algeria return
to calmness at the 17th annual Franco-Italian summit held in
Chambery, southeast France.
</P>
<P>
"The president of the Italian council (prime minister) Romano
Prodi has proposed bringing all his assistance in the limit of his
possibilities to try to allow this country (Algeria) recover its
calmness," said Chirac at a press conference held after he joined
the summit.
</P>
<P>
Chirac said that the historical relations of Algeria with Italy
are different from those with France, Rome can play a good role in
helping Algeria solve its six-year conflict between the government
and Islamic militant groups.
</P>
<P>
"All that Italy can do in this sense will go in the good
sense. We hope that Italy could, taking into account its
historical context different from that of France in respect of
Algeria, be an element of reason and calmness in the relations
between Algeria and the world," he said.
</P>
<P>
Chirac said that both France and Italy condemn "all
atrocities" which took place in Algeria.

