<HEADLINE> New Book on Lee Kuan Yew Launched in Singapore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, October 3 (Xinhua) -- A new book on Senior Minister
Lee Kuan Yew of Singapore was launched here today, marking what is
called "the first attempt to organize systematically the Senior
Minister's many ideas".
</P>
<P>
Published by the Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) and the Times
Publishing Group, the 400-page book, entitled "Lee Kuan Yew: The
man and his ideas", tells of the events, people and political
fortunes that were to shape Lee's view of the world, as well as
the path he set for the transformation of Singapore.
</P>
<P>
Based on 13 fresh and exclusive interviews with Lee, the most
extensive he has ever given, the book chronicles Lee's life and
ideas, from his early political awakening in Cambridge to his
present position as an elder statesman.
</P>
<P>
"I believe this book fills an important gap for those who want
to understand him, what his key ideas are and how he came to form
them," Lim Kim San, executive chairman of the SPH said at the
launching ceremony.
</P>
<P>
"More important, it should satisfy those who want to understand
Singapore itself, how it came about and what makes it tick," he
added.
</P>
<P>
At an earlier press conference, Han Fook Kwang, one of the
three authors of the book, said that while other books had been
written about Mr. Lee, the new book was the first attempt to
organize systematically the Senior Minister's many ideas.
</P>
<P>
To do so, the authors read more than 2,000 speeches made over
50 years of Lee's career, he said. The other two authors are
Warren Fernandez and Sumiko Tan. All the three authors are Straits
Times journalists.  
</P>
</TEXT>
