<HEADLINE> New Constituent Stock for Hang Seng China Enterprises Index </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 3 (Xinhua) -- HSI Services Ltd. announced
here today that the Hang Seng China Enterprises Index (HSCEI) will
have a new constituent stock next week.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan Expressway Company Ltd. will be listed on the Stock
Exchange of Hong Kong next Tuesday and be included as a
constituent stock of the HSCEI with effect from next Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
With the addition of Sichuan Expressway, a company based in the
southwestern Chinese province of Sichuan, there will be 36
constituent stocks in the HSCEI, which is to track the overall
performance of all China enterprises listed in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The index is managed and compiled by HSI Services Ltd., which
also compiles the Hang Seng Index, the barometer of the local
stock market, as well as Hang Seng MidCap 50 Index and Hang Seng
China-Affiliated Corporations Index.
</P>
<P>
HSI Services Ltd. is a wholly-owned subsidiary of Hang Seng
Bank. 
