<HEADLINE> Courier Moves up to Semifinals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Jim Courier of the
United States took a straight-set win Friday over Jan Kroslak of
Slovakia to enter the semifinals at the China Open indoor
tournament.
</P>
<P>
The Former world top player Courier, who played more patient
than his young rival, sealed the victory 6-4, 6-3 in 70 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Courier steered seven aces and his first serve percentage was
as high as 85% -- 25% higher than the Slovakian's.
</P>
<P>
Kroslak, this year's Shanghai Open champion, dominated the net
in the first set. His strong and precise straight-line shots kept
Courier on watching at the line. But his 18 unforced errors ruined
his advantage on the net and baseliners and lost the set.
</P>
<P>
The 24-year-old Kroslak came back in the second set to break
first, but soon double faulted awa=0y at 1-1. Courier broke again
at 5-3 through Kroslak's another double fault and took the match
on his service.
</P>
<P>
"I got into his service game more than he was able to get into
mine," said Courier after his win. "But Kroslak played pretty
well. I was not sure whether I could close up the match at the
end."
</P>
<P>
Courier had played just at Doha and Los Angles this year. He
was confident with his performance in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
"I was from feast to famine in the past. I just hope to keep
lining like this."
</P>
<P>
Earlier Friday, Kenneth Carlsen of Denmark edged Alex O'Brien
of the United States 7-5, 5-7, 7-6 (7-4) in the longest match on
the China's ATP Tour.
</P>
<P>
Carlsen stormed 11 aces to one in the two hours and 56 minutes
match. Carlsen, who ranks 90th in the world, rushed more to the
net than the American, who is the world 82nd.
</P>
<P>
In two other quarterfinals, fifth seed Magnus Gustafsson of
Sweden ousted Byron Black of Zimbabwe 6-4, 6-3, while third-seeded
Thomas Johansson of Sweden won 6-2, 6-4 over Italian Gianluca
Pozzi.
</P>
<P>
Courier faces Johansson in Saturday's semifinals and Carlsen
will play Gustafsson.
</P>
<P>
In Friday's only doubles semifinal match, top seeds M. Bhupathi
and Leander of India scored a 6-4, 6-4 triumph over M. Keil and
T.J. Middleton of the United States.
</P>
<P>
Courier and Alex O'Brien will meet Australia's A. Florent and
J. Eagle in the other doubles semifinal Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
