<HEADLINE> China Investment Policy Seminar to Be Held in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Senior officials from the
Central Government will come to Hong Kong and brief local
businessmen on the latest investment environment and policy of
the inland next week at the "97 China Investment Seminar", a
senior Hong Kong trade official told reporters here today.
</P>
<P>
The seminar is co-organized by the Ministry of Foreign Trade
and Economic Cooperation (MOFTEC) and Hong Kong Trade Development
Council (TDC), said TDC assistant executive director Mimi Yueng at
a press conference today.
</P>
<P>
The seminar will be held in conjunction with the "97' China
(Hong Kong) Investment Symposium".
</P>
<P>
A delegation of 250 members from 29 provinces, municipalities
and autonomous regions, led by An Min, Assistant Minister of the
MOFTEC, will arrive here for the symposium, bringing along almost
900 investment projects.
</P>
<P>
In addition to traditional processing industries such as food
and textile, the delegation will also offer projects in
architecture and construction, oil and biochemical production,
agriculture, forestry, animal husbandry and fishery, metallurgical
industry, machinery, electrical and electronic equipment, power
generation, gas and water works.
</P>
<P>
The seminar and the symposium, which are scheduled for October
7 to 11, will be the first large trade promotion event organized
by the MOFTEC in Hong Kong after Hong Kong's return to the
motherland, Hu Jingyan, deputy director general of the Foreign
Investment Administration of the MOFTEC, said at the press
conference.  
