<HEADLINE> Export-Oriented Economy Brings Profound Changes to Fujian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, October 3 (Xinhua) -- A booming export-oriented economy
is bringing big changes to east China's Fujian Province, the home
of many overseas Chinese and Chinese nationals residing abroad.
</P>
<P>
To late last May, 21,000 overseas-funded enterprises have
received approval from relevant authorities in the province, and
they involved a total of 19 billion US dollars. The industrial
volume and exports of these enterprises accounted for more than 50
percent or 60 percent respectively of Fujian's total last year.
</P>
<P>
The exports volume exceeded 10 billion US dollars in 1996, and
the exports in the first five months of this year increased by 30
percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
As a result, many industrial sectors and rural departments have
set up joint-ventures for manufacturing toys, shoes and caps,
electronic and machinery products.
</P>
<P>
In addition, a lot of local state-run enterprises and private
companies have adopted the international ISO-90000 Standard, and
are keen on hiring employees who are fluent in foreign languages.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
