<HEADLINE> Belarus Angered by Lukashenko's Aborted Trip to Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Belarus protested to Russia today
for aborting the visit of President Alexandr Lukashenko to the
Russian cities of Lipetsk and Yaroslavl, reports said.
</P>
<P>
All Belarussian state-owned media carried Lukashenko's
telegrams to Russian President Boris Yeltsin and to the mayors of
Lipetsk and Yaroslavl, as well as a note from the Belarussian
Foreign Ministry to his Russian counterpart about Lukashenko's
visit, the Itar Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Belarus blamed Russia for denying Lukashenko permission to
visit by linking it with the release of Russian journalist Pavel
Sheremet, who was kept in prison in Belarus' Grodno and charged
with illegally crossing the Belarussian-Lithuanian border.
</P>
<P>
Grodno regional prosecutor Leonid Tereshchenko told reporters
that Sheremet, who has been in detention for more than two months,
could be released in one or two weeks after "investigation
materials come to the prosecutor's office." 
</P>
