<HEADLINE> China to Reform Teacher Training Methods </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, October 3 (Xinhua) -- The State Education Commission
has announced that it will reform the teachers' colleges in China.
</P>
<P>
The plan will target the old-fashioned curriculums, textbooks
and teaching methods, for the purpose of improving the quality of
the country's would-be primary and high school teachers.
</P>
<P>
China has been reforming its primary and high schools for
several years to keep up with the changes in the society. However,
the teachers' colleges in China have remained underdeveloped.
</P>
<P>
The problems include a lack of flexibility and variety in
teaching methods, and the specialities cover narrow knowledge and
fields, according to the reform plan.
</P>
<P>
A feasibility study was completed last month to set the goals
of the reform, and a guiding committee consisting of top-rated
scientists and experts has been formed, commission officials
revealed.
</P>
<P>
The commission is to raise a big sum of funding for the
reform. 
</P>
</TEXT>
