<HEADLINE> China Develops 60 Types of Military Airplanes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 3 (Xinhua) -- China has developed more than 60
types of military airplanes over the past 46 years, today's
Economic Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
The paper says that the country's aviation industry, which was
created in 1951, now boasts 110 enterprises and 34 research
institutes with 560,000 scientists, technicians and workers.
</P>
<P>
China now has a full range of military planes, including
fighters, attackers, bombers, freighters, trainers and
helicopters, the paper says.
</P>
<P>
The country has also made progress in producing different types
of civilian airplanes, including the famous Yun series. The Yun-7
transport airplanes have been exported to some countries, the
paper adds.
</P>
<P>
The sector is now converting its technology for manufacturing
products for civilian use. Some 80 percent of its output value
comes from the production of civilian products, the paper says.
</P>
