<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Beats Saudi Arabia 1-0 in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, October 3 (Xinhua) -- China beat Saudi Arabia 1-0 in a
rain-soaked Asian qualifying group A match on Friday to keep its
World Cup hopes alive.
</P>
<P>
Defender Zhang Enhua headed the winning ball past goalkeeper
Mohammed Al-Al-Daye in the 69th minute on a corner kick delivered
by midfielder Li Ming.
</P>
<P>
The goal sent about 30,000 Chinese fans at Jinzhou Stadium,
northeastern city of Dalian, into ecstacy as China desperately
needed a victory after drawing away with Qatar and losing home to
Iran in the previous group matches of the Asian Zone World Cup
Qualifying final round.
</P>
<P>
The first half saw the two sides battled evenly in rain. Then
China beefed up offence in the second half to frequently pound the
Saudi Arabian defence and finally found the chance to score.
</P>
<P>
The visitors' best opportunity came in the 82nd minute when the
64th-minute substitute Youssef Al-Thyniyan delivered a free kick
flying just a little high over the bar.
</P>
<P>
Midfielder Khalid Al-Temawi also had a chance in the 33rd
minute from the right in the penalty area but his blast was too
wide.
</P>
<P>
"It was a good match. We showed high speed in switching between
offence and defence," said Chinese coach Qi Wusheng. "All my
players did not relax for one single second through the whole
match. But somehow we put the heavy psychological burden aside."
</P>
<P>
He praised the scorer, saying it is also Zhang who had scored
the first goal with an almost identical header on a same right
corner kick at last year's Asia Cup quarterfinals, where the Saudi
team won 4-3 over China.
</P>
<P>
"China played very well in the second half," Saudi Arabia's
head coach Nilo Vingada said. "We were ready to play this kind of
game, but players are not computers and they could make
mistakes. The whole team was responsible for the loss."
</P>
<P>
"We lost the game but the war (to qualify for the finals in
France) is not lost yet," Vingada added.
</P>
<P>
China now collects four points from one victory, one draw and
one loss, same as Saudi Arabia, who took part in the 1994 World
Cup finals in the United States.
</P>
<P>
The two sides will meet again on November 6, when Saudi Arabia
play as the host. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
