protest the use of forged Canadian passports in a reputed
attempt to assassinate a leader of the Islamic militant group
Hamas in Jordan.
</P>
<P>
The Wall Street Journal
</P>
<P>
-- President Clinton would put pressure on other nations to
allow U.S. inspections of their farms. Last year, 38 percent of
fruits and 12 percent of vegetables eaten in the U.S. came from
abroad. double the 1986 level. But the U.S. could face a backlash
over the plan, as has already occurred with similar rules for
meat. In a related development, South Korea suspended imports of
beef from Nebraska after finding E. coli bacteria in a shipment.
