<HEADLINE> Macao Airport Cargo Shipment Doubles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, October 3 (Xinhua) -- The amount of cargo shipment
through the Macao International Airport reached 30,061 tons in the
first nine months of the year, more than double that in the same
period of last year.
</P>
<P>
A press release from the Macao International Airport Company
(CAM) said today that the amount of shipment from January to
September was a 122 percent increase from the same period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
In September alone, the airport shipped 4,741 tons of goods, a
record since the airport started its commercial operation in
November 1995.
</P>
<P>
The CAM authorities estimate that the throughput would continue
to post strong growth in the coming two months as the
pre-Christmas retail sale period is drawing near.
</P>
<P>
Currently, several large cargo air services are using the
airport. They include the Scandinavian Airlines System, Asiana
Cargo, Federal Express, and Evergreen International.
</P>
