<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 3 (Xinhua) -- A Saudi Arabian airlines
aircraft made a full emergency landing in the early hours today at
the airport in Chennai, capital of India's Tamil Nadu state,
following a fire warning, Press Trust of India said.
</P>
<P>
The Boeing 747, which was operating between Jeddah and
Singapore, landed with 320 passengers on board safely, airport
sources said.
</P>
<P>
When a fire warning was received from the cargo hold of the
aircraft, the pilot informed the Chennai air traffic control who
in turn alerted all the emergency departments including fire and
medical services.
</P>
<P>
The aircraft was then cleared for landing at 3:40 a.m. local
time, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
All the 320 passengers bound for Singapore were transferred to
another Saudi Arabian aircraft which took off at 10 a.m.
</P>
<P>
The snag of the aircraft is being rectified, the sources added.
 
