higher but remained range bound today as it continued to benefit
from a surge in the gold price this week.
</P>
<P>
The local unit closed at 72.86 US cents from 72.77 at
Thursday's close. It was trapped in a tight range of 72.75 to
72.95 US cents in local trading with traders saying continued
speculation that the Reserve Bank will further cut interest rates
held back the local unit.
</P>
