<HEADLINE> Salaries for Zambian Ministers to Be increased </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lusaka, October 3 (Xinhua) -- A bill to increase salaries and
allowances for Zambia's vice-president, parliament speakers and
ministers has been prepared, Zambia Daily Mail reported today.
</P>
<P>
Under the bill, the vice-president will get a total month
income of 641,666 Kwacha (about 493 U.S. dollars), including
325,000 Kwacha salary, 266,666 Kwacha special allowances and
50,000 Kwacha postal allowances.
</P>
<P>
The parliament speaker's month saraly has been pegged at
266,666 Kwacha with special allowances of 250,000 Kwacha and
50,000 kwacha as postal allowances.
</P>
<P>
Cabinet ministers will be entitled to monthly salary of
208,333 Kwacha, special allowances 233,333 kwacha and postal
allowances of 50,000 Kwacha.
</P>
<P>
Zambian government officials usually have their own companies
and factories or farms. When government ministers declared their
assets in January this year, Zambian Science, Technology and
Vocational Training Minister declared assts amounting 11 billion
Kwacha (about 8.5 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Under another bill presented to the parliament, retired
speaker will be entitled to a tax free monthly salary at 80
percent of the incumbent's emoluments if he does not hold any
political office after his retirement.
</P>
<P>
The retired speaker will also be entitled to a house in an
area of his choice but at reasonable cost, a furnished office
with personal secretary and a messenger in addition of a cook,
laundry man, gardener and a domestic servant.
</P>
<P>
The retired speaker will be given two vehicles with two
drivers with running and maintenance expenses to be met by the
government with cabinet approval. 
</P>
