President Laurent-Desire Kabila of the Democratic Republic of Congo
had decided to send ``a detachment of military observers to take
account of the origins of the shellings and the possibility of
destroying them.'' The announcement of this military intervention
was made Wednesday evening at a joint press conference by Kabila and
Congolese President Pascal Lissouba, who made a brief visit to
Kinshasa.
</P>
