<HEADLINE> Port Authority Set up to Oversee Trans-regional Container Ports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 3 (Xinhua) -- A port authority designed to
oversee some of China's busiest container ship terminals was
inaugurated in Shanghai earlier this week.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Joint Port Authority is responsible for the
planning, construction, and coordination of the deep-water
container ship ports in Shanghai city and Jiangsu and Zhejiang
provinces.
</P>
<P>
"Its inauguration marks a step forward for turning Shanghai
into an international shipping center," said Vice-premier Wu
Bangguo while attending the inauguration ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Because of its importance, Premier Li Peng wrote a few words of
encouragement for it.
</P>
<P>
Members of the new organization include container terminals in
Shanghai, Ningbo, Nanjing, Zhenjiang, Zhangjiagang and Nantong,
and the managing committee is composed of officials from the
Ministry of Communications and from Shanghai, Zhejiang and Jiangsu
provinces. 
</P>
