<HEADLINE> U.S. President Pays Respects to China on National Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 3 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton has
sent a message here expressing his best wishes on China's 48th
National Day, which fell on October 1.
</P>
<P>
In the message to Chinese President Jiang Zemin, Clinton said
he wished Chinese people the best on the occasion of celebrating
the country's "rich history" and "many achievements."
</P>
<P>
"Deepening cooperation between the People's Republic of China
and the United States will contribute to the peace and prosperity
of the people of both our nations and the entire world," he said.
</P>
<P>
Clinton also said he was looking forward to seeing Jiang at
their planned meeting later this month in Washington. 
</P>
</TEXT>
