<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT, October 3 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Canada has recalled its ambassador to Israel to
protest against the reportedly use of forged Canadian passports by
Israeli agents who tried to kill Hamas member in Amman last week,
Israel Radio reported today.
</P>
<P>
The radio quoted Canadian officials as saying that Canada has
taken a grave view of the matter after determining neither the
two attackers were Canadian nationals. (Canada-Israel-Passports)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Any military alliance in the Asia-Pacific region
should be defensive, transparent and not directed at third
countries, a Russian Foreign Ministry spokesman said today.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on a new joint defense treaty signed by the United
States and Japan on September 23, the spokesman said that the
agreement specifies the two countries' joint military operations
against sudden accidents but doesn't implicate the overseas use of
the Japan's Self-Defense Forces. (Russia-U.S.-Japanese Alliance)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- At least five people were killed and four others
went missing after a motor boat carrying 48 students collided
with a freighter on the Musi River, Indonesia's South Sumatra
Province, on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman for the South Sumatra District Police Sardjo Sadjad
said thick smog caused by forest fires was to blame for the
accident, reports reaching here today from Palembang, South
Sumatra, said. (Indonesia-Boat Collision)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- A United States Navy F-14 Tomcat fighter crashed
in the Atlantic Ocean off the East Coast today during a training
mission.
</P>
<P>
Both crew members ejected from the plane. One was rescued by
the Coast Guard and a search was under way for the
other. (US-Fighter-Crash)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BRASILIA -- Seven people died when a Xinguh model plane crashed
Wednesday night in the western region of the state of Santa
Catarina in southern Brazil, the Brazil news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The news agency said that when the aircraft went down, six
persons died immediately, and one was seriously injured. The
injured died later at the regional hospital of Chapeco City.
(Brazil-Air Crash)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
YANGON -- Some 15 armed members of the Kayin National Union
(KNU) attacked a village in Myanmar's Kayin State Thursday,
killing six persons and wounding three others, official sources
said today.
</P>
<P>
The group of KNU's 16th Battalion, led by War Nay Phu, raided
Mi Ka Thit Village housing a break-away faction of the KNU led by
U Saw Tha Mu He, who traded their arms for peace with the
government in February. (Myanmar-KNU-Attack)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO -- U.S. President Bill Clinton will visit Brazil
from October 13 to 15 and meet his Brazilian counterpart Fernando
Henrique Cardoso, the Brazilian Foreign Ministry announced today.
</P>
<P>
Clinton and Cardoso will witness the signing of several
bilateral agreements, including those on education, clean and
nuclear energies and juridical assistance. (Brazil-US-Visit)
</P>
</TEXT>
