<HEADLINE> Uganda to Ban Smoking in Public Places </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, October 3 (Xinhua) -- A bill banning smoking in
Uganda's public places will soon be tabled in parliament, local
daily The New Vision reported today.
</P>
<P>
Officials from the Ministry of Health were quoted here on
Thursday as saying that the ministry will later embark on total
eradication of smoking in the country.
</P>
<P>
Kihumuro Apuuli, Director General in the Ministry of Health,
pointed out that his ministry has produced a paper on tobacco
recommending a ban of smoking in public places. The
ministry will soon seek approval from cabinet to enact the law,
he added.
</P>
<P>
Smoking is a major cause for cancer in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
