<HEADLINE> French Foreign Minister to Visit S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, October 3 (Xinhua) -- French Foreign Minister
Hubert Vedrine will visit South Africa next Thursday, French
Ambassador Tristan d'Albis announced in Pretoria.
</P>
<P>
Local media today quoted the envoy as saying that the problems
suffered by African countries would be the core of Vedrine's
talks with his South African host and counterpart, Alfred Nzo.
</P>
<P>
"We would like to establish all-level permanent dialogue
between France and South Africa (on African issues)," said the
ambassador.
</P>
<P>
Tristan d'Albis said that France "cared for Africa and its problems",
and South Africa had shared with France this care and concern.
</P>
<P>
D'albis said France was not in favour of bilateral commissions
because it favored a more pragmatic and realistic way of
handling African issues.
</P>
<P>
Vedrine will also meet South African Deputy President Thabo
Mbeki and the parliamentary Foreign Affairs Committee before
leaving for Addis Ababa, Ethiopia, for a meeting with Salim Ahmed
Salim, Secretary General of the Organisation of African Unity.
</P>
<P>
During his three-day African trip, the French Foreign Minister
will also spend one day in Ivory Coast before returning to
Paris. 
</P>
</TEXT>
