<HEADLINE> Zimbabwean Riot Police Clash with University </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, October 3 (Xinhua) -- The Zimbabwean riot police
Thursday fired
tear gas at students from the University of Zimbabwe who were
stoning cars in and outside the campus, the Zimbabwe
News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
No official comment could be obtained on why the students were
stoning cars, but sources at the campus said the students wanted
to march into Harare Town to demonstrate, but police were
blocking their way.
</P>
<P>
Some of the students boycotted classes this week demanding to
have their grants restored in full. Most of the students who
attended classes were those who were preparing for final
examinations next month.
</P>
<P>
Security guards at the university's entrance gates were
advising people not to enter the campus as it was enveloped in
tear gas smoke.
</P>
<P>
Students who managed to escape from the campus alleged that
the police were also assaulting them. 
</P>
</TEXT>
