<HEADLINE> NZ Stocks Finish Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Activity in the afternoon
pushed the New Zealand sharemarket higher today after a quiet
start in the morning. However, the trading value was moderate.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 index ended 18 points higher at 2,593 with a
turnover of nearly 44 million NZ dollars (28 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Telecom shares led the rises, up 11 cents to 810 cents. Also
higher were Fletcher Building, gaining 4c to 512c, Brierley
Investment, edging up 1c to 139c and Carter Holt Harvey, climbing
11c to 355c.
</P>
<P>
Among other leaders, Air New Zealand remained unchanged at 276c
and Lion Nathan slipped 2c to 382c.
</P>
<P>
There were 56 rises and 45 falls.  
</P>
</TEXT>
