<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe to Implement Rural Electrification </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe will spend over 37
million U.S. Dollars over the next 10 years in electrificying the
country's rural areas, the Zimababwean Transport and Energy
Minister said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The 10-year rural electrification program to be carried out in
two phases will cover 328 centres in rural areas, Transport and
Energy Minister Enos Chilowore said.
</P>
<P>
The first phase running up to the year 2002 will cost 174
million Zimbabwe Dollars (14 million U.S.Dollars), and the second
phase, which will run from 2002 to 2007, will electrify 78
schemes covering 128 centres at a cost of 286 million Zimbabwe
Dollars (23 million U.S.Dollars), Chikowore added.
</P>
<P>
The implementation of the program comes as a result of the the
study on the rural electrification masterplan concluded in May
this year, said the minister. 
</P>
</TEXT>
