<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand's Automotive Product Exports Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Thailand exported 15.18 billion
baht (433.6 million U.S. dollars) worth of automotive products in
the first eight months of this year, a jump of 145.38 percent over
a year earlier, according to an automobile industry organization.
</P>
<P>
The Automobile Industry Club of the Federation of Thai
Industries said the automotive products include
completely-built-up (CBU) cars, car engines and parts,
motorcycles, completely-knock-down (CKD) kits and spare parts.
</P>
<P>
Thailand exported 23,940 CBU cars worth 8.07 billion baht
(230.6 million dollars) during the first eight months of this
year. Compared with the same period of 1996, the number of cars
rose by 19,809 units or 479.52 percent and the value by 6.95
billion baht (198.7 million dollars) or 622.10 percent, the local
press today quoted Surapong, spokesman for the federation, as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Exports of car engines and parts reached 1.26 billion baht
(35.9 million dollars) and 1.47 billion baht (41.8 million
dollars) for the period, up by 152.83 percent and 389.68 percent
respectively from a year ago, Surapong said.
</P>
<P>
He said 85,120 motorcycles worth 2.83 billion baht (80.7
million dollars) were also shipped overseas for the period, down
from the same period of last year by 43,510 units or 33.63 percent
in number and by 1.16 billion baht (33.1 million dollars) or 29.10
percent in value.
</P>
<P>
Export of motorcycle CKD kits totaled 1.31 billion baht (37.3
million dollars), up by 1.10 billion baht (31.4 million dollars),
while spare parts totaled 247.01 million baht (7.05 million
dollars), up 213.48 percent, Surapong said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
