<HEADLINE> Japanese Grant for Sri Lankan University </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 3 (Xinhua) -- The Japanese government has
granted 200,000 U.S. dollars to Sri Lanka's Peradeniya University
to modernize the laboratory and other facilities in its faculty of
agriculture.
</P>
<P>
An agreement on the grant was signed in the university
Thursday, the local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
Peradeniya University, established in 1947 and located in
Kandy, 110 kilometers from here, has the oldest faculty for
agricultural studies in the country.
</P>
<P>
Nichiman Corporation of Japan will be responsible for supplying
modern educational equipment to the university, including both
laboratory and video equipment necessary for research work to be
carried out.
</P>
<P>
Every year the Japanese government provides funds for priority
projects of the Sri Lankan government.
</P>
<P>
The recently-established Medical Faculty of Sri Lankan
Jayawardhanapura University received a grant of 250,000 dollars
this year, which would be used to supply equipment to the faculty
and to upgrade the Colombo South Teaching Hospital.  
</P>
</TEXT>
