<HEADLINE> Cholera Cases Discovered in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 3 (Xinhua) -- An outbreak of cholera in Sri
Lanka is being feared following the discovery of nine persons
suffering from the disease, according to Health Ministry sources
today.
</P>
<P>
Eight of the cases were found in Chilaw in the northwestern
coast of the country, more than 70 kilometers from here, and one
at Wattala in the northern suburb of Colombo, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The patients are being treated at the infectious disease
hospital in the country, the sources said, adding that the
ministry appointed a special team to treat the disease on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
While an inquiry is being conducted by the health authorities
about the cause of the recurrence of the disease in Sri Lanka
after a period of more than 40 years, the public are being warned
of the dangers of the disease and measures to be taken to prevent
it from spreading.  
</P>
