<HEADLINE> More Guangzhou People Embark on Outbound Travel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, October 3 (Xinhua) -- More and more people from this
prosperous city in south China are planning to travel overseas.
</P>
<P>
Over the past five years, more than one million people from
Guangzhou have gone out of the boundary to do business, engage in
sightseeing and visit relatives.
</P>
<P>
When the city began to open to the outside world in 1983, the
citizens could only visit Hongkong and Macao. Now tourist
destinations have been extended to Singapore, Malaysia, Thailand,
the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Travel to the European countries, the US, Canada, Australia,
New Zealand, Japan and the Republic of Korea is also allowed on a
trial basis.
</P>
<P>
While outbound travelers could only ask their overseas
relatives or friends to buy bills for them at the beginning, now
most of them pay the tours by themselves, since travel agencies
from 1989 began to accept local payments.
</P>
<P>
Of the one million outbound tourists in the past five years,
over 110,000 went out of the country for business talks, study
tours, professional training, exhibitions and trade fairs. 
</P>
