total foreign debts of 97 billion U.S. dollars, of which 50
percent are owed to Japanese creditors, according to the Board of
Investment.
</P>
<P>
Auto parts producers in Thailand are currently operating at
half capacity. It is feared that if the economic downturn
continues through next year, many factories will be forced to
close, laying off thousands of workers. Under such circumstances,
increased exports will be the only way to keep the factories open.
</P>
