<HEADLINE> U.S. Navy F-14 Crashes off East Coast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 2 (Xinhua) -- A United States Navy F-14
Tomcat fighter crashed in the Atlantic Ocean off the East Coast
today during a training mission.
</P>
<P>
Both crew members ejected from the plane. One was rescued by
the Coast Guard and a search was under way for the other.
</P>
<P>
The plane was on a routine training mission with other aircraft
when it went down about 4 p.m. EDT (2000 GMT) off the coast of
North Carolina or Virginia.
</P>
<P>
The fighter was assigned to the Oceana Naval Air Station at
Virginia Beach.
</P>
<P>
An investigation to determine the cause of the crash was under
way. 
</P>
