<HEADLINE> Semi-final Lineups Fixed for Women's European Volleyball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, October 2 (Xinhua) -- Semi-final lineups for the 20th
Women's European Volleyball Championships were decided on
Thursday as Croatia and Russia both booked their berths with 100
percent records.
</P>
<P>
The Croats needed 105 minutes to hold off a tough Italian
challenge 16-14, 14-16, 15-13, 15-7 in the last round of gourp B
matches which also qualified host nation the Czech Republic.
</P>
<P>
The hosts, despite losing 15-11, 14-16, 11-15, 12-15 Thursday
night to Ukraine, still managed to advance as group B second
placers.
</P>
<P>
They edged out Italy which registered the same 3-2 record but
lost out with their 0-3 defeat by the Czechs to blame.
</P>
<P>
Russia had an easier day to maintain their perfect group
record with a comfortable 3-0 victory over Poland. Bulgaria,
with a 3-2 group record, also got promotion second behind Russia.
</P>
<P>
Saturday's semi-finals will see Czech Republic take on Russia
and Croatia entertain Bulgaria.
</P>
<P>
The champions of the tournament will be determined on October
5. 
