<HEADLINE> Turtle Eggs Planted on Mexican Beaches </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, October 2 (Xinhua) -- Mexican authorities for
marine life protection have placed 38,522 turtle eggs in the
beaches of the northern state of Sinaloa, it was officially
announced today.
</P>
<P>
The Sinaloa state Citizenship Protection Secretariat said in a
report that the eggs were placed on the beaches of Ceuta in the
Elota municipality.
</P>
<P>
It added that the operation started at the beginning of June
and will continue until the end of October when the number of
incubated eggs could increase to 40,000.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, besides the placing of eggs on the
beaches, the authorities have also dispatched police units to
patrol the areas concerned around the clock. 
