<HEADLINE> Shining Path Guerrillas Kill 12 Peasants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, October 2 (Xinhua) -- Peru's Shining Path guerrillas
killed 12 peasants last week in Tingo Maria, a village in central
Peru, Peruvian police reported today.
</P>
<P>
The victims included five members of the Self-Defense
Committees who were charged with "collaborating with police" by
Shining Path activists.
</P>
<P>
Shining Path guerrillas, armed with submachine guns and hand
guns, enter communities at any time of the day in groups of 15 to
18.
</P>
<P>
Some 500 peasants have abandoned their land in Huanuco where
the village of Tingo Maria is located for fear of guerrilla
attacks.  
</P>
