<HEADLINE> Seven Killed in Air Crash in Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, October 2 (Xinhua) -- Seven people died when a Xinguh
model plane crashed Wednesday night in the western region of the
state of Santa Catarina in southern Brazil, the Brazil news agency
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The news agency said that when the aircraft went down, six
persons died immediately, and one was seriously injured. The
injured died later at the regional hospital of Chapeco City.
</P>
<P>
It said that the plane fell on trees at a site one kilometer
from the Chapeco airport several minutes before landing.
</P>
<P>
The news agency quoted Chapeco city officials as saying that
strong rains and bad weather might have been the cause of the
mishap.
</P>
<P>
According to the news agency, the Brazilian Aeronautics
Ministry has formed a group of technicians to investigate the
cause of the accident. The plane was owned by the Santa Catarina
state government. 
</P>
