<HEADLINE> 5 Killed in Philippine Hostage Drama </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 3 (Xinhua) -- A desperate man held six people
hostage in a house in a town north of Manila Thursday night and
shot dead four of them in a shooting spree before killing himself,
police confirmed today.
</P>
<P>
Police said Nixon Tagyan, 34, armed with a 0.45 caliber pistol,
herded at gun point his estranged wife, daughter, parents-in-law,
sister-in-law and a maid last night into the house in a village in
Bulacan town.
</P>
<P>
Tagyan went berserk after his wife refused to give him a sum of
money. He shot indiscriminately at his captives, slaying four and
wounding his sister-in-law, police said. But the maid managed to
escape.
</P>
<P>
Tagyan then shot himself out of frustration.  
</P>
