<HEADLINE> Brazil Posts Huge Foreign Trade Deficit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, October 2 (Xinhua) -- Brazil registered a big deficit
of 1.283 billion U.S. dollars in its September foreign trade, the
Brazilian Industry, Commerce and Tourism Ministry reported today.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said in a press release that the country's exports
amounted to 4.588 billion dollars and imports were worth 5.871
billion dollars in September.
</P>
<P>
The trade deficit accumulated in the first nine months of this
year reached 6.23 billion dollars, according to the ministry.
</P>
<P>
Brazilian economic experts estimate that the country's foreign
trade deficit for the whole of this year could be over 10 billion
dollars. 
</P>
