<HEADLINE> Inflation in Russia Down in September </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, October 2 (Xinhua) -- Consumer prices in Russia dropped
0.3 percent in September, bringing the inflation rate over the
first nine months of this year down to 9.1 percent, a report of
the State Statistics Committee said today.
</P>
<P>
The Itar-Tass news agency quoted the report as saying prices
for goods and services have fallen in 58 out of 89 regions or
districts across the Russian Federation.
</P>
<P>
The greatest decline of 2.2 percent was registered in the
Ust-Ordynski Buryat Autonomous District, followed by the regions
of Chita, Magadan and Samara, with a decline of 1.3-1.7 percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
