<HEADLINE> Dow Nudges Ahead as Other Indexes Edge Toward New </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, October 2 (Xinhua) -- The Dow Jones industrial
average rose 12.03 points to 8,027.53 in mild trading today as a
couple of other indexes set new records.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by about 11 to 8 on the
New York Stock Exchange, where volume came to 474.76 million
shares, well below the 597.89 million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The technology-laden Nasdaq composite rose 12.07 to 1,702.37,
topping its past high of 1,697.36, set on September 23.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE composite rose 2.35 to 503.43, beating its record
close Wednesday, and the Amex composite rose 1.69 to 704.96 for
its second consecutive closing record.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list rose 3.01 to 958.42.
</P>
</TEXT>
